image.altText: A man stands posing for a photo on a wooden walkway in front of trees, wearing a white shirt and dark pants.

props.synopsis: A Perth man accused of the manslaughter of his partner's 11-year-old son is released from custody, after the charges against him were dropped due to a lack of evidence against him.

title.children: Manslaughter charge dropped against stepfather accused of neglecting boy left quadraplegic

image.altText: Image of the beach at Red Bluff, on Quobba Station north of Carnarvon.

props.synopsis: The 30-year-old man disappeared while diving near Red Bluff on Tuesday afternoon, with police divers now en route to assist with the search.

title.children: Police search underway for diver missing off WA's Gascoyne coast

image.altText: Rebecca Boehm stares glumly out kitchen window of her Bentley apartment.

props.synopsis: The reality of owning a strata-managed apartment after having saved for it for over a decade has been nothing short of a nightmare for single Perth mother and primary school teacher Rebecca Boehm.

title.children: Rebecca saved for 10 years to afford her dream home, but living in it has become a nightmare

image.altText: A silhouette stature of a man holding a spear in front of a sunset.

props.synopsis: An Aboriginal organisation in the remote WA town of Roebourne says it is spending $50,000 a year helping its members cope with extreme heat.

title.children: Outback town's residents brace for 'steaming' summer after record-breaking winter heat

image.altText: A red-and-white banner held up at an AFL game.

props.synopsis: The WA Sydney Swans Supporters Club, who support the AFL team they love from 3,000 kilometres away, have been awarded Supporter Group of the Year for the club's sense of community and inclusivity.

title.children: Die-hard Sydney Swans group supports AFL team from other side of Australia

image.altText: People gather outside a hospital where there's a sign that reads "red zone".

props.synopsis: Hezbollah opted for using pagers instead of mobile phones as a way to avoid being tracked and spied on. But the devices have become the target of a large-scale attack, leaving at least nine dead and thousands injured.

title.children: Hezbollah thought pagers would be safer than mobiles — until the devices exploded across Lebanon

image.altText: A harvest moon over London Heathrow airport in 2017. A plane flies in front

props.synopsis: The harvest supermoon will be at its biggest and brightest tonight but it's bad news for those in Australia hoping to catch a partial lunar eclipse too.

title.children: Everything to know about the harvest supermoon set to dazzle stargazers tonight

image.altText: A green crocodile leather bag sits on display in front of a vinnie's sign saying it's $2000

props.synopsis: A keen-eyed worker at an op shop spotted a "designer" find that retails for $4,000. The handbag, believed to have been made by luxury brand Balenciaga, was put on sale for half that price, but the store has received backlash on social media.

title.children: Is $2,000 too much to pay for a handbag at an op shop?

image.altText: A Beaufort Bomber aircraft

props.synopsis: During World War II, a Beaufort Bomber aircraft took off from Busselton's air force base in WA. Descendants of the missing passengers are now spearheading the effort to locate it.

title.children: At the height of WWII, a bomber took off from southern WA. What happened to it remains a mystery

image.altText: A group of men cross or raise their arms while standing in front of a makeshift blockade made of timber.

props.synopsis: There are concerns for dozens of Australian and New Zealander hikers on the Kokoda Track after local landowners set up a blockade, forcing authorities to suddenly close the famous route in Papua New Guinea.

title.children: Concerns for 'exhausted' Australian hikers as landowners form Kokoda Track blockade

image.altText: A man is led out of a house in handcuffs.

props.synopsis: An Australian man has been arrested and charged over allegedly running an encrypted communications network tailored specifically for the use of criminal organisations.

title.children: Syndicate 'dismantled' as AFP raids target Australian creator of app for criminals

image.altText: Harris speaks into a microphone in front of a red American flag wearing a beige suit

props.synopsis: Kamala Harris's bid for the US presidency has become a key target of Russian disinformation campaigners focusing on the Democratic campaign, Microsoft says.

title.children: Microsoft says Kamala Harris's campaign target for Russian disinformation after deepfake video spreads

image.altText: Albanese presser stern

props.synopsis: The federal government has failed to bring its first home buyer support scheme to a vote in the Senate, with the Greens and the Coalition voting together to delay consideration of the legislation for two months.

title.children: The government has been unable to bring on a vote that would have killed its own housing policy

image.altText: Toddlers play around a table. A mother is with her child, and a woman dressed in purple monitors.

props.synopsis: Nearly all families would benefit from a lift to childcare subsidies recommended by the Productivity Commission, with free care for low-income families.

title.children: Free child care for families earning under $80,000, landmark report recommends

props.synopsis: Footage is released of a man being tackled to the ground by a transit guard at a Perth train station, breaking his collarbone, in an incident the Corruption and Crime Commission described as '"excessive".

title.children: 'Prolific fare evader' tackled to ground at train station in incident probed by anti-corruption agency

image.altText: A blue board shows a photo of Epstein and Maxwell hugging, beside a series of dot-pointed text. A hand points to the photo..

props.synopsis: A three-judge panel ruled on Thursday to uphold Ghislaine Maxwell's sex trafficking conviction for helping the late financier Jeffrey Epstein abuse underage girls.

title.children: British socialite Ghislaine Maxwell denied appeal on sex trafficking conviction

image.altText: Felicity sits at a desk and smiles as Edit  stands behind her with a hand on her chair in a bleak looking office.

props.synopsis: The trailer for the highly anticipated Australian version of The Office is here and we have thoughts. So many thoughts, it warranted an article.

title.children: The eight things everyone is thinking after watching The Office Australia trailer

image.altText: A worker wearing a hard hat with the CFMEU logo emblazoned across it.

props.synopsis: After findings of "lawlessness" and bikie infiltration within the CFMEU, the federal government will seek to reset relations with a high-level meeting between ministers, unions and business next month.

title.children: 'Reset' meeting to be held between unions, business and government after CFMEU scandal

image.altText: Jacqui Lambie parliament

props.synopsis: The review found a widely held perception that the military justice system was too closely linked to the defence force's top brass.

title.children: Lambie blasts government after royal commission accidentally leaks secret report

image.altText: Kitchen bench top

props.synopsis: Australia is the first country to prohibit fake stone, as the final step in a national crackdown on the deadly dust disease silicosis.

title.children: Fake kitchen stone to be stopped at border from January 1

image.altText: A still from a video appearing to show a fighter plane approaching another aircraft

props.synopsis: The 2022 incident involved a People's Liberation Army aircraft firing flares near the RAAF plane, before cutting in front of it and releasing "chaff" into its flight path.

title.children: Video emerges appearing to show 'dangerous' Chinese intercept of 'enemy' Australian aircraft

image.altText: A cow in a paddock standing next to a large blue machine.

props.synopsis: The agriculture industry is a huge greenhouse gas emitter. This breath testing machine gives farmers a real-time record of cattle methane emissions, so they can take measures to reduce them.

title.children: Breath testing cattle to battle climate change

image.altText: CCTV of people shopping at a grocery store.

props.synopsis: Someone appears to have intercepted and placed explosives in a shipment of pagers that Hezbollah purchased for the express purpose of avoiding Israeli surveillance of their mobile communications. The fallout will be significant.

title.children: 'Hezbollah is not only looking over its shoulder, but feeling vulnerable': What the pager attack was really about

image.altText: A man holds open an empty wallet.

props.synopsis: The rocketing price of housing and rapid inflation in prices for unavoidable goods, such as food and fuel, have created a cost-of-living crisis. And this has gone on to fuel a generational split in income.

title.children: Why an imperfect storm has hit younger people in this economy

image.altText: Half of a white metal hull with debris around it lies on the ocean floor, with blue water and harsh light

props.synopsis: The deaths of five people could have been avoided, a former OceanGate employee has told an inquiry into the Titan submersible implosion.

title.children: 'Very little in the way of science' in Titan submersible's construction, inquiry hears

image.altText: Fuel pumps

props.synopsis: Motorists can expect further reprieve at the petrol bowser with analysts predicting continued falls in the price of oil. But economists say while falling prices are good for consumers, it won't lower underlying inflation as far as the Reserve Bank wants it to, meaning interest rate cuts are still unlikely until next year.

title.children: The price you pay for petrol is set to fall even further in coming weeks

image.altText: Three women with their faces covered sit at a table and draw on paper

props.synopsis: Women living under a regime which banned them from using their voice in public risk punishment to tell the world the brutal, bleak truth of life in Afghanistan.

title.children: Afghan women's mental health deteriorates under new laws banning the sound of their voices

image.altText: People walk across the street towards Flinders Street Station.

props.synopsis: Economists are warning unemployment rates could go through the roof if "labour hoarding" is proven among Australian firms.

title.children: We could be sitting on an unemployment time bomb, economists warn

image.altText: A woman in a wedding dress and holding a bouquet stands beside a man in a jacket and tie outside a gift shop

props.synopsis: We've crunched the numbers for more than 43,000 job combinations and 2.8 million couples (including 31,600 same-sex couples). Turns out it's not just lawyers, doctors or teachers who stick to their own when it comes to love.

title.children: Who you'll probably marry, based on your job

image.altText: Moira Deeming arrives at day three of the defamation hearing with her lawyer.

props.synopsis: Expelled Liberal MP Moira Deeming has been grilled in court over whether she was aware a member of a far-right-group had spoken at a US Let Women Speak rally, before she helped to organise one in Melbourne.

title.children: Ousted Victorian Liberal MP Moira Deeming questioned over role in organising anti-trans-rights rally

image.altText: A man looks at a share price board outside the ASX in Sydney.

props.synopsis: Australian stocks are flat in afternoon trade, while traders are betting the US Federal Reserve will deliver a supersized interest rate cut. Follow the latest updates in our live blog.

title.children: ASX flat ahead of US Fed interest rate decision, Wall Street nearly unchanged

liveBlogKeyEvents.title: A sneak peek of tonight's The Business
Australian Banking Association appoints new Deputy Chair

image.altText: A young child sleeps and a sleeping mother is just visible behind them, in a room dimly lit.

props.synopsis: Parents who co-sleep with their young children can face judgement and criticism, especially when the children are primary-school aged. Yet, most people in the world co-sleep with their children at some point. Here's what some of those parents get out of it.

title.children: How old is too old for co-sleeping? The answer may divide parents

image.altText: Teal PMs Allegra Spender, Monique Ryan, Sophie Scamps, Kylea Tink, Kate Chaney and Zali Steggall at a press conference

props.synopsis: We live in an age that favours disruptors. In politics, in business, in media, in art and even sport. And there's precious little evidence to suggest that we're finished with them yet.

title.children: For better or worse, the Teals have been stirring up the back bench

image.altText: A court sketch of Ryan W. Routh, suspected of attempting to assassinate Donald Trump.

props.synopsis: The suspect in an apparent assassination attempt on Donald Trump has appeared in court. This is what we learned from Mr Routh's first court appearance, documents provided to the court, and what could happen next.

title.children: What the court documents tell us about the apparent second attempt on Trump's life
